29 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
30 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
31 Article – State Finance and Procurement
32 3–101.
33 (a) In this title the following words have the meanings indicated.
34 (b) “Department” means the Department of Budget and Management.
35 (c) “Secretary” means the Secretary of Budget and Management.

SENATE BILL 858 3
1 SUBTITLE 4. AUDIT AND FINANCE COMPLIANCE UNIT.
2 3–401.
3 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE, THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
4 INDICATED.
5 (B) “AGENCY” MEANS AN ENTITY OF THE EXECUTIVE BRANCH OF STATE
6 GOVERNMENT.
7 (C) “UNIT” MEANS THE AUDIT AND FINANCE COMPLIANCE UNIT.
8 3–402.
9 THERE IS AN AUDIT AND FINANCE COMPLIANCE UNIT IN THE DEPARTMENT.
10 3–403.
11 (A) IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1224(H)(1) OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT
12 ARTICLE, THE GOVERNOR SHALL IMPLEMENT SYSTEMS AND PROCESSES TO
13 MONITOR THE EFFORTS OF THE EXECUTIVE DEPARTMENTAL UNITS TO CORRECT
14 AUDIT FINDINGS REPORTED BY THE OFFICE OF LEGISLATIVE AUDITS.
15 (B) THE UNIT IS RESPONSIBLE FOR MONITORING THE EFFORTS OF
16 AGENCIES EXECUTIVE DEPARTMENTAL UNITS IN CORRECTING AUDIT FINDINGS
17 REPORTED BY THE OFFICE OF LEGISLATIVE AUDITS IN ACCORDANCE WITH TITLE
18 2, SUBTITLE 12, PART IV OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE.
19 3–404.
20 (A) IN CARRYING OUT ITS RESPONSIBILITIES, THE UNIT SHALL ASSIST
21 AGENCIES EXECUTIVE DEPARTMENTAL UNITS WITH THE RESOLUTION OF AUDIT
22 FINDINGS BY:
23 (1) PROVIDING OBJECTIVE ASSESSMENT OF CORRECTIVE ACTIONS;
24 AND
25 (2) MONITORING PROGRESS IN THE IMPLEMENTATION OF
26 CORRECTIVE ACTIONS.
27 (B) THE UNIT MAY IMPLEMENT PROACTIVE STEPS TO ADDRESS AND
28 PREVENT AUDIT FINDINGS THROUGH ADVICE AND SUPPORT PROVIDED TO
29 AGENCIES PROVIDE GUIDANCE, COORDINATION, AND TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE TO

4 SENATE BILL 858
1 EXECUTIVE DEPARTMENTAL UNITS TO STRENGTHEN EFFORTS TO ADDRESS AND
2 PREVENT AUDIT FINDINGS AND TO STRENGTHEN INTERNAL CONTROLS AND
3 COMPLIANCE PRACTICES.
4 3–405.
5 (A) THE UNIT SHALL PROVIDE DIRECT ASSISTANCE TO AGENCIES
6 EXECUTIVE DEPARTMENTAL UNITS WITH:
7 (1) FOUR OR MORE REPEAT AUDIT FINDINGS; OR
8 (2) AS REQUESTED BY THE JOINT AUDIT AND EVALUATION
9 COMMITTEE UNSATISFACTORY AUDITS.
10 (B) THE DIRECT ASSISTANCE PROVIDED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS
11 SECTION SHALL INCLUDE:
12 (1) ADVICE AND SUPPORT TO DEVELOP CORRECTIVE ACTIONS AS
13 SOON AS PRACTICABLE, A REVIEW OF THE TIMELINE DEVELOPED BY THE
14 EXECUTIVE DEPARTMENTAL UNIT FOR THE IMPLEMENTATION OF CORRECTIVE
15 ACTIONS FOR EACH RECOMMENDATION TO ENSURE THAT THE TIMELINE HAS
16 ACHIEVABLE COMPLETION DATES;
17 (2) A REVIEW OF RESOLUTION ACTIONS ON EACH FINDING WITH A
18 FOCUS ON REPEAT AND SIGNIFICANT FINDINGS TO PROVIDE ADVICE AND SUPPORT
19 IN ASSISTING WITH THE DEVELOPMENT OF CORRECTIVE ACTIONS;
20 (3) PERFORMING SAMPLE TESTS OF IMPLEMENTED CORRECTIVE
21 ACTIONS, AS NEEDED; AND
22 (4) MONITORING PROGRESS IN OF THE IMPLEMENTATION OF
23 CORRECTION CORRECTIVE ACTIONS UNTIL THE LEGISLATIVE AUDITORS RETURN TO
24 BEGIN THE NEXT RELATED FISCAL COMPLIANCE AUDIT.
25 (C) (1) THE UNIT SHALL ESTABLISH A SPECIALIZED TEAM TO PROVIDE
26 THE DIRECT ASSISTANCE REQUIRED UNDER THIS SECTION.
27 (2) THE SPECIALIZED TEAM ESTABLISHED IN PARAGRAPH (1) OF
28 THIS SUBSECTION MAY INCLUDE CURRENT STATE EMPLOYEES, CURRENT
29 CONTRACTUAL EMPLOYEES, AND EXTERNAL CONTRACTORS.
30 3–406.

SENATE BILL 858 5
1 (A) THE UNIT SHALL MAINTAIN A DASHBOARD ON CURRENT AND REPEAT
2 AUDIT FINDINGS ON ITS WEBSITE.
3 (B) (1) THE DASHBOARD REQUIRED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS
4 SECTION SHALL INCLUDE ALL AUDIT FINDINGS FOR AGENCIES UNDER
5 EXAMINATION EACH YEAR, ORGANIZED BY UNITS OF THE AGENCY.
6 (2) FOR EACH FINDING, THE DASHBOARD SHALL INCLUDE:
7 (A) ON OR BEFORE OCTOBER 1 EACH YEAR, THE UNIT SHALL SUBMIT AN
8 ANNUAL REPORT TO THE JOINT AUDIT AND EVALUATION COMMITTEE, IN
9 ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, ON ALL AUDIT
10 FINDINGS FOR EXECUTIVE DEPARTMENTAL UNITS UNDER EXAMINATION.
11 (B) THE REPORT SHALL INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING INFORMATION FOR
12 EACH FINDING:
13 (I) (1) THE RECOMMENDATIONS OF THE OFFICE OF
14 LEGISLATIVE AUDITS;
15 (II) (2) THE NUMBER OF YEARS THAT A REPEAT FINDING
16 REMAINS UNRESOLVED;
17 (III) (3) THE PROJECTED COMPLETION DATE OF THE FOR
18 RESOLUTION OF A FINDING;
19 (IV) (4) INFORMATION ON UNRESOLVED FINDINGS,
20 INCLUDING THE REASON A FINDING IS UNRESOLVED; AND
21 (V) (5) A GRAPHIC REPRESENTATION OF THE PROGRESS OF
22 CORRECTIVE ACTIONS THAT INCLUDES WHETHER THE FINDING IS UNRESOLVED, IN
23 PROGRESS, OR RESOLVED THE PROGRESS OF CORRECTIVE ACTIONS THAT INCLUDES
24 WHETHER THE FINDING IS UNRESOLVED, IN PROGRESS, OR RESOLVED.
25 (C) THE DASHBOARD SHALL BE FULLY OPERATIONAL ON OR BEFORE
26 OCTOBER 1, 2027.
27 3–407.
28 THE SECRETARY MAY ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY OUT THIS SUBTITLE.
29 Article – State Government

6 SENATE BILL 858
1 2–1224.
2 (h) (1) The Governor and the Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of Maryland
3 shall implement systems and processes to monitor the efforts of the Executive
4 Departmental Units and the Judiciary, respectively, to correct audit findings reported by
5 the Office of Legislative Audits.
6 (i) (1) A report auditing a unit of State or local government shall have any
7 cybersecurity findings redacted in a manner consistent with auditing best practices before
8 the report is made available to the public.
9 (2) AN UNREDACTED CYBERSECURITY FINDING IN A REPORT
10 AUDITING A UNIT OF STATE OR LOCAL GOVERNMENT MAY BE VIEWED BY:
11 (I) MEMBERS OF THE JOINT AUDIT AND EVALUATION
12 COMMITTEE;
13 (II) MEMBERS OF THE JOINT COMMITTEE ON CYBERSECURITY,
14 INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, AND BIOTECHNOLOGY;
15 (III) THE CHAIR AND THE SUBCOMMITTEE CHAIRS OF THE
16 SENATE BUDGET AND TAXATION COMMITTEE;
17 (IV) THE CHAIR AND THE SUBCOMMITTEE CHAIRS OF THE
18 HOUSE APPROPRIATIONS COMMITTEE;
19 (V) THE GOVERNOR, THE GOVERNOR’S CHIEF OF STAFF, AND
20 THE GOVERNOR’S DEPUTY CHIEFS OF STAFF; AND
21 (VI) THE AUDIT AND FINANCE COMPLIANCE UNIT IN THE
22 DEPARTMENT OF BUDGET AND MANAGEMENT.
23 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, on or before October 1, 2026,
24 and October 1, 2027, the Audit and Finance Compliance Unit shall report to the Joint Audit
25 and Evaluation Committee, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article,
26 on the status of the dashboard required under § 3–406 of the State Finance and
27 Procurement Article, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act.
28 SECTION 3. 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
29 July 1, 2026.

